      "solution": "def read_float():\n    return float(input())\n\nweight_kg = read_float()\ndose_mg = read_float()\nconc = read_float()\n\ndose = dose_mg / 2 if weight_kg < 40 else dose_mg\nvolume = (weight_kg * dose) / conc\n\nif volume > 30:\n    print(\"OVERDOSE\")\nelif volume < 5:\n    print(\"UNDERDOSE\")\nelse:\n    print(f\"{volume:.1f}\")",
      "statement": "Calculate the volume of medication to administer to a patient.\nIf [[weightKg]] is less than {{40}} kg, [[doseMg]] is halved.\nIf the volume exceeds {{30}} ml, output {{OVERDOSE}}.\nIf the volume is below {{5}} ml, output {{UNDERDOSE}}.\nOtherwise, Output the volume in ml rounded to 1 decimal place (e.g. 10.67 → 10.7).\n\n<<Rules:>>\n- volume (ml) = ([[weightKg]] × [[doseMg]]) / [[conc]]",
