    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Calculate the volume of medication to administer to a patient.<br>If <var>weightKg</var> is less than <const>40</const> kg, <var>doseMg</var> is halved.<br>If the volume exceeds <const>30</const> ml, output <const>OVERDOSE</const>.<br>If the volume is below <const>5</const> ml, output <const>UNDERDOSE</const>.<br>Otherwise, Output the volume in ml rounded to 1 decimal place (e.g. 10.67 &rarr; 10.7).<br><br><strong>Rules:</strong><br>- volume (ml) = (<var>weightKg</var> &times; <var>doseMg</var>) / <var>conc</var></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer <var>weightKg</var> for the weight in kg.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> An integer <var>doseMg</var> for the dose in mg/kg.<br><strong>Line 3:</strong> An integer <var>conc</var> for the drug concentration in mg/ml.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">The volume in ml rounded to 1 decimal place, <const>OVERDOSE</const>, or <const>UNDERDOSE</const>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>weightKg</var> &le; 100<br>1 &le; <var>doseMg</var> &le; 100<br>1 &le; <var>conc</var> &le; 100</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">70\n5\n25</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n     